  "text": "The standard reverse transcriptase activity assay was adapted from [CITATION_1] . An aliquot of the harvest (35 Al) was mixed with a cocktail reaction in a final volume of 100 Al (final concentration: 10 AM dTTP, 50 mM TrisHCl, pH 8.3, 3 mM MgCl 2 , 5 mM DTT, 0.1 mg/ml bovine serum albumin, 0.05% Nonidet P-40, 20 Ag/ml poly (rA)!dT 12-18 (Roche) and 4 ACi [ 3 H]dTTP (Perkin-Elmer, 88 Ci/mmol)). The reaction was incubated for 1 h at 37 8C, followed by the addition of a freshly made solution of MnCl 2 at a final concentration of 2 mM for 15 min. Precipitates were formed by adding trichloroacetic acid (12.5% w/v), sodium pyrophosphate (50 mM) and baker's yeast tRNA (0.5 mg) in a final volume of 1 ml. The mixture was kept on ice for 2 h and filtered through glass microfibre filters 934-AH (Whatman). The radioactivity was counted in a Liquid Scintillation Counter Rackbeta1217 (Perkin Elmer).",
